SIMPLE: outline
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outline
<hw>Out"line`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>The line which marks the outer limits of an object or figure; the
exterior line or edge; contour.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>In art: A line
drawn by pencil, pen, graver, or the like, by which the boundary of a
figure is indicated.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A sketch composed of such
lines; the delineation of a figure without shading.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Painters, by their <qex>outlines</qex>, colors, lights, and
shadows, represent the same in their pictures.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: A sketch of any scheme; a preliminary or
general indication of a plan, system, discourse, course of thought,
etc.; <as>as, the <ex>outline</ex> of a speech</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But that larger grief . . .⟦br⟧
Is given in <qex>outline</qex> and no more.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sketch; draught; delineation. See
<er>Sketch</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outline</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outline
<hw>Out"line`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Outlined</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Outlining</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To draw the outline
of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: To sketch out or indicate as by an outline; to
create a general framework of (a plan, system, discourse, course of
thought), for which the details need to be added; <as>as, to
<ex>outline</ex> an argument or a campaign</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outlinear</ent>⟦br⟧
